a, b, c = {'a': 1}, {'b': 2}, {'c': 3}
d, e, f = {'d': 4}, {'e': 5}, {'f': 6}
old_list = [a, b, c, d, e]
new_list = [a, c, d, f, e]
expected_changes = [{'count': 1, 'value': [a]}, {'count': 1, 'value': [b],
    'removed': True, 'added': None}, {'count': 2, 'value': [c, d]}, {
    'count': 1, 'value': [f], 'removed': None, 'added': True}, {'count': 1,
    'value': [e]}]
self.check_changes(old_list, tuple(new_list), expected_changes)
self.check_changes(tuple(old_list), iter(new_list), expected_changes)
self.check_changes(iter(old_list), new_list, expected_changes)
